    <string name="open_help">
        <b>Application Notifications:</b>
        \n
        For applications notifications to work,
        you must turn on "Notification Access" for the Open Fit application.
        This is commonly found at: Settings>Notifications>Notification Access.
        \n\n
        <b>Connection Problems:</b>
        \n
        If you cannot pair with Gear Fit from Open Fit application,
        go to bluetooth settings, make sure the Gear Fit is not on the list of paired devices,
        If it is you may need to remove it(see note below),
        Then scan and pair to the Gear Fit. 
        the pairing will succeed but the Gear Fit will show \'waiting for confirmation..\'.
        Wait for it to fail and the screen on the Gear Fit will change.
        Then open the Open Fit app and scan, select device, and connect.
        \n\n
        <b>Note:</b> Deleting the Gear Fit from the paired devices in bluetooth settings,
        will cause a reset to the Gear Fit.
    </string>
